This paper deals with social choice theory, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of social welfare functions, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and decision-making algorithms (cs.DS). The paper's focus on convex preferences and the existence of maximal elements suggests a connection to optimization and convex optimization, which are relevant to machine learning and data science (cs.SI, cs.LG).
